## ğŸ— Database Design

A relational database structure ensures scalability, data integrity, and efficient management of users, properties, bookings, payments, and reviews.

---

### 1. Users
**Fields**
- id (PK)
- name
- email
- role (Host, Guest, Admin)
- created_at

**Relationships**
- One user owns many properties  
- One user creates many bookings  
- One user writes many reviews  

---

### 2. Properties
**Fields**
- id (PK)
- owner_id (FK â†’ users)
- title
- location
- price

**Relationships**
- One property belongs to one user  
- One property has many bookings  
- One property has many reviews  

---

### 3. Bookings
**Fields**
- id (PK)
- user_id (FK â†’ users)
- property_id (FK â†’ properties)
- check_in_date
- check_out_date
- status (pending, confirmed, canceled)

**Relationships**
- One user â†’ many bookings  
- One property â†’ many bookings  
- One booking â†’ one payment  

---

### 4. Payments
**Fields**
- id (PK)
- booking_id (FK â†’ bookings)
- amount
- status (Paid, Failed, Refunded)
- payment_date

**Relationships**
- One booking â†’ one payment  

---

### 5. Reviews
**Fields**
- id (PK)
- user_id (FK â†’ users)
- property_id (FK â†’ properties)
- rating
- comment

**Relationships**
- One user â†’ many reviews  
- One property â†’ many reviews  
